deck: A teenage Cree superheroine with season-based powers who joins The Justice League United.
description:
Current Events

  • Justice League United - Miiyahbin has joined up with Alanna Strange seeking help to stop the Whitago monster that has been terrorizing her and her family. She is also having a hard time controlling her powers causing her to seek help from the Justice League United and later join them. See the Justice League of Canada written by Jeff Lemire.
  • The New 52: Futures End - Miiyahbin was seen to be a member on The Justice League of America when Firestorm quit the League after Green Arrows "death". See the story arc Futures End written by Jeff Lemire , Brian Azzarello , Dan Jurgens and Keith Giffen.
  • Convergence- Miiyahbin, as a member of the Justice League United, is one of the heroes to observe the emergence of Telos into her universe in Convergence #6 by Jeff King and Scott Lobdell.

Creation

Prior to release, Justice League United was originally going to be the latest volume of Justice League of America retitled "Justice League of Canada" following the events of Forever Evil, and as such, creator Jeff Lemire wanted to create a new character that represented the native people of Canada, his home country. In order to make sure he depicted Cree culture faithfully and with respect, Lemire took many trips to the Cree community of Moose Factory where he'd teach art classes to many of the children, while getting their input on what they'd like to see in a superhero who represented their culture. In the end, both Equinox's appearance and seasonal power set were heavily influenced by what Lemire learned from the Cree people in Moose Factory.

Major Story Lines

Justice League Canada

They introduce Miiyahbin Marten leaving her school with her friend in Moose factory Island, her friend was trying to talk to her however she was very distracted and decided to go straight home like her granny asked. When she got home there was someone waiting for her asking for her help. Telling her that it was too late, that the Whitago is here, telling her to say the word as he transforms into some kind of beast, she then yells "KEEWAHTIN" and transforms blasting him with some sort of energy, he then transforms to look like her telling her that she can't run from herself, it then appeared as it was all a vision and her granny came to comfort her.

Miiyahbin and her friend Heather discover the base and explain that it was part of an old NATO radar base from the 80's, there they are attacked by the creature she saw before, flying, propelled by smoke, and takes Miiyahbin. Miiyahbin wakes up frozen into the wall of a cave and an old man wakes her up calling her granddaughter. Miiyahbin is confused as he isn't her granddad, and asks who he is, to which he answers, he is one of "The Seven". Miiyahbin hears the Whitago coming back and begs for help, he tells her only she can save herself with a word. The man explains that the seven live within all "our" people, but she is special, because within her also lives the beast, the Whitago.

Alanna Strange finds herself in the Bunker after being Zeta beamed from Rann, and puts on a suit that is just like Adam Strange's after hearing nearby sounds, and finds Miiyahbin's friend Heather and agrees to help find her. While following tracks outside they encounter the Whitago and Alannas blaster is able to deter it, however it keeps returning, so they hurry and are able to find the cave Miiyahbin is trapped in. They find Miiyahbin and offer to try and melt the ice, but she is just scared of what will happen when she says the word, as she knows only she can stop the Whitago, but as it approaches she knows she has to say it and is able to stop the Whitago with a single blast, shortly before passing out. Alanna Is able to carry Miiyahbin back to the bunker just after the members of Justice League United return and decide on a name. Miiyahbin discovers that her grandmother was her predecessor as Equinox and that her long lost father was ultimately the Whitago. Through this, she accepts her powers and place in Justice League United by freeing her father.

deck: The cosmic embodiment of all possibilities and the lover of Eternity.
description:
Origin

The Never Queen is a cosmic being that seeks the power source of The Impericon. Zed, leader of The Impericon, uses The Motivator to convince heroes from various worlds to become Champions that he can send to battle The Never Queen. After the Silver Surfer agrees to be a Champion of The Impericon and face The Never Queen, he sees the all-too-brief battle the previous Champion had.

The Surfer soon discovers the truth. The Impericon is powered by the Never Queen's heart, which was cut out and stolen by Zed with the Edge of Reality, a weapon from another universe capable of cutting through the fabric of reality. Without her heart, the Queen of Nevers will ultimately die, and with her all that could be.

Powers & Abilities

The Queen of Nevers is the embodiment of all possibility. She is cosmically aware and knows everything that can or will happen. She is infinitely sorrowful for all the possibilities that die every moment (that which never was or almost was).

The Queen of Nevers can project all possible futures and outcomes into a beings consciousness, overwhelming them with both positive and negative emotions.

deck: Danny Milligan and Carol Faber were the two humans that were the templates for Cloud.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Danny Milligan is a normal human in a relationship with Carol Faber. One day they are driving along when their car went off the road. The sentient nebula Cloud, who is coming to Earth seeking help for a cosmic problem, and is unfamiliar with humans, comes into contact with them. Sensing their fear, she helps them, but also goes partly insane due to absorbing their fear. She takes on Carol's form (and later, sometimes Danny's) and loses her memory before being brainwashed by the Secret Empire.

Carol and Danny, meanwhile, survive in comas. After some years, Cloud's memory returns with the help of Seraph and the Defenders, and they find Carol and Danny, but are unable to help them.

Some time after that, Moondragon, who is possessed by the Dragon of the Moon, taunts Iceman (who loves Cloud) by putting Carol and Danny in danger. The Dragon is defeated and in her last act, Moondragon heals Carol and Danny, bringing them back to consciousness.
name: Danny Milligan

description:
Origin

While attempting to mug a women Alpha arrived and after a brief confrontation Andy punched him in the face, cracking his skull. He is then rushed to Pittsburgh University Medical Center, where he was expected to make a recovery. However, for some unknown reason, the mugger mutates into a giant tumorous monster. After absorbing the life-force of many already in the hospital, Zeta sets out to consume the city. Teaming-up with Spider-Man, Alpha arrives and the two manage to defeat Zeta, but fail to completely destroy all his cancerous tissue, allowing Zeta to escape.

deck: A plane technician who worked for Warren Worthington III (Angel) and was infected with gamma spores.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Chris Larmouth grew up wanting to be a super-hero. He works out and drinks horrible protein shakes in order to get as close as he can to his heroes. He even took a job as the Defenders' pilot in the hopes that maybe someday something might happen, and enjoys his job.

Then one day he eats some alfalfa sprouts that he had grown, which were infected by some gamma spores that came from Ephraim Soles. Larmouth's body starts growing muscles for a brief moment, and he thinks he is finally becoming a super-hero--until he erupts in plant tentacles and writhes in pain.

Beast and Iceman see him, and Iceman puts him in a cryogenic freeze so they can study and hopefully heal him. After defeating the giant plant monster that is created by the spores, they bring him up to the team's infirmary.

There they put him in a cryogenic chamber. For a long time, Beast tries to find a cure for him, but can't, and he becomes a symbol of some of Beast's failed hopes.

Eventually, the Dragon of the Moon (who is possessing Moondragon) brings Chris to a pocket dimension, where his cryogenic chamber is turned off. Beast can fight the Dragon, or help Chris. Since other Defenders stop the Dragon, Beast helps Chris re-freeze. Then, when the Dragon is defeated, Moondragon uses her power to fully heal Chris (and some others) before she is turned to ash.
name: Chris Larmouth

deck: A wealthy man born in 18th century London who made a deal with a demon on his deathbed to be bought back to life but only if someone summons him back.
description:
Origin

Hotspur was originally a nobleman in London in the 1700s. He led a gang of other peers called the Lords of Fun, who were extreme libertines and did whatever they wanted, to whoever they wanted. He also dabbled in the dark arts, and made a deal with a demon on his deathbed to return to life if he was ever summoned.

In modern times, a believer in past lives did just that, and Hotspur once again lived--now with great demonic powers that he learned in hell. His believes that fun is the most important thing.

Major Story Arcs

Now living in 20th-century New York, he continues his life as a libertine, going to dance clubs and slashing the other participants, while using his mystical hypnotic powers to keep them unaware of what was going on.

However, the newly arrived Andromeda, undercover as a surface-dweller, notices what was going on. She confronts him and he runs off to Central Park, where he has a huge group of hypnotized people, all in a frenzy of demonic worship.

The Defenders attack, but Hotspur uses his illusions to defeat or hold off most of them until Andromeda shows up in costume. She seems to injure him, but he heals. The rest of the Defenders rally, but Hotspur once again creates illusions to defy them. Then they are grabbed by his Hades Engine, which negates all their powers. They are rescued by an ersatz Nick Fury, who supplies them all with guns and urges them to shoot into an oncoming tide of demons.

The Defenders finally wake up from this final illusion and realize that the demon horde is just the hypnotized civilians--and the Hades Engine is just a bunch of junk. At wit's end, Gargoyle incites Cloud to use her lightning in combination with his bio-mystical bolts, and they weaken Hotspur and finally drive his demonic powers away, leaving him once again fully mortal.

Powers and Abilities

Hotspur is a mortal with powers gained in hell. His powers largely lie in illusions and hypnosis. His illusions are very persuasive, and capable of making people believe they are feeling great pain or ignore actual pain, can feel incapacitated, see things that are not there, and believe their powers do not work. They can be pushed into a feeling of ecstasy and be made to do what he wants. He can create individually-tailored illusions, or affect large crowds at once. His illusions work even on mystical or telepathic beings such as Gargoyle, Valkyrie, and Cloud. However people can see through his illusions given great enough concentration.

He can also blast soul-fire, similar to Daimon Hellstrom's hellfire.

He is capable of healing his body mystically, even from a broken arm.
name: Hotspur

deck: A Celestial Spirit owned by Lucy Heartfilia. She is one of the 12 Golden Zodiac Keys, she controls water. She recently sacrificed her freedom to summon the Celestial King Spirit, having Lucy break her key. She has a vicious temper. She was previously owned by Lucy's mother, Layla.
description:
Appearance

Aquarius is a Celestial Spirit with the appearance of a royal blue Siren. She has a Aquarius zodiac symbol tattoo on her collar bone.

Personality

Aquarius is a very moody and ill-tempered Celestial Spirit who often threatens to kill her Lucy. Unlike other Celestial spirit who serves and obeys Lucy, Aquarius is irritated by Lucy. When she is summoned, she will either attack the opponent or Lucy or both depending on her mood. She is sweet, loving and caring to her Boyfriend Scorpio to which she shows her other different side.

History

Her previous owner was Lucy Heartfilia's mother, Layla Hearfilia who Aquarius deeply cared for. When Layla retired, Aquarius' key was entrusted to another mage who was instructed to give her key to Lucy if Lucy decides to become a mage. Aquarius' is Lucy's first celestial spirit and key.
name: Aquarius

deck: The other masked rider of old California
description:
Origin

El Coyote is the masked persona of Don Csar de Echage, a rich California landowner who after studying in Spain returns to his lands in California in 1851 and finds that while he was away it has been invaded and conquered by Yankees obsessed with taking hold of the gold mines owned by the Hispanic inhabitants of the newly incorporated territory.

To fight this Don Csar leads a double life: as a cowardly hidalgo and as an intrepid and fearless champion of the rights of the Hispanos, in the guise of El Coyote, with mask and cloak, and Leonor de Acevedo for a girlfriend, his arch enemy is the ruthless General Clarke from America.

Creators

El Coyote was a Spanish language Pulp hero written by Jos Mallorqu Figuerola (1913-1972) starting in 1944 the character appeared in 192 novels and later appearing in two different comic book series, as far as I know they have never been translated into English; however they have appeared in German translations.
name: El Coyote

deck: Out of the Zone of Darkness with Justice!
description:
Origin

Mscara Negra is really judge Elodia Zrate who lives in Madrid, Spain, she took on her persona of The "Black Mask" because of the criminals she saw getting away with their crimes, it also helps that she has access to something called el Zona de la Oscuridad, the Zone of Darkness, Which gives her the ability to teleport herself and others for long distances though the Zone, also by focusing her willpower she can crate shadow creatures which have no intelligence of their own but obey limited orders from her, and she can also create areas of complete darkness that can be used to trap people, along with all that she is also a competent hand to hand combatant, and carries a .45 caliber automatic.

Creators

Mscara Negra was a superheroine who appeared in the pages of the first El Coyote comics series that ran from 1947 to 1955.
name: Mscara Negra
